===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considers it to be an area word.

Within {{cog|sit}}, Chinese, {{cog|bo|-}}{{,}} and {{cog|sit-tan}} have a final ''*-k'', while other Tibeto-Burman languages have open syllables; compare {{cog|bo|ལྡུགས||to pour}}, {{cog|sit-tan-pro|*lɯk||to pour}}, {{cog|sit-pro|*r-lu(w)||to pour; to bathe}} (whence {{cog|njm|tr=rəlu|t=to pour}}, {{cog|grt|rua|t=to pour}}, {{cog|ksw|tr=lu|t=to pour}}, {{cog|mjw|tr=iŋ lú|t=to bathe; to wash}}) ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT).

Outside of {{cog|sit}}, compare words in the {{cog|mkh-pea}} languages, such as {{cog|cog|tr=kʰruk|t=to pour}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

It is unclear how and whether {{och-l|冶|to smelt; to cast}} is related ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

